articles.title: Indian American Arrested In New Jersey In $13 Million Tech Fraud - NDTV
articles.description: An Indian American has been arrested in New Jersey on charge of being part of a technical support scam that targeted more than 7,000 victims defrauding them of more than USD 13 million, a US Attorney announced Thursday.
articles.content:
The count of conspiracy to commit wire fraud carries a maximum penalty of 20 years in prison.
